radiographic_examinations.findings: Moderate atelectasis in the dependent areas of bilateral lung bases; high-density fluid in the gallbladder fossa, perihepatic and subhepatic areas; moderate amount of free fluid in the pelvis; liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and reproductive organs within normal limits; no evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation; no abdominal aortic aneurysm.
